# Systemd user preset for Mackes Shell.
#
# Fedora's systemd-preset mechanism reads files under
# /usr/lib/systemd/user-preset/ in lexical order to decide whether a
# unit is enabled by default for new users. `enable` here means
# "enable this user unit on first encounter unless the user has
# explicitly disabled it." Existing installs are unaffected — preset
# only governs first-time enable decisions.
#
# 1.1.0 — User reported the mesh clipboard wasn't running after a
# fresh install. The clipboard daemon's `WantedBy=graphical-session
# .target` requires that the unit be enabled in the user's systemd
# instance; shipping the unit file alone wasn't enough. This preset
# closes that gap for new accounts; mackes-enforce-session enables
# it explicitly for existing accounts on the next login.

enable mackes-clipboard-daemon.service
enable mackes-gvfsd-mesh.service
enable mackes-remmina-sync.service
enable mackes-remmina-sync.timer
enable mackes-media-sync.service
enable mackes-media-sync.timer

# Phase 13.5 — KDE Connect bridge user unit (1.1.0+).
enable mackesd-kdc-bridge.service
